PART 5: PENROSE TILINGS AND TOURNAMENT Q-SPECTRUM
======================================================================

The Penrose tiling diffraction pattern has peaks at:
  positions q = h + k·τ where τ = 1/φ
  intensities ∝ |sin(mπτ)/sin(πτ)|²

This is EXACTLY our Q_k formula with k → τ = 1/φ!

Which k/p is closest to 1/φ = 0.618...?
