PART 6: PHYLLOTAXIS — BIOLOGICAL FIBONACCI
======================================================================

Phyllotaxis analogy:
  Sunflower seeds → tournament vertices (on circle)
  Golden angle → Fibonacci permutation
  Optimal packing → maximum H

  Interval: connect to NEAREST neighbors → CONCENTRATED
  Paley: connect via QR → SCATTERED (Ramanujan expander)

  Phyllotaxis says: golden-angle placement is optimal
  Tournaments say: Interval (consecutive) is optimal for H

  KEY DIFFERENCE: phyllotaxis optimizes PACKING,
  tournaments optimize HAMILTONIAN PATHS
  But both relate to the golden ratio!

