PART 8: FREE ENERGY — THERMODYNAMIC ANALOGY
======================================================================

Thermodynamic analogy:
  Lattice gas on Ω(T) at activity z = 2:
  Z(z) = I(Ω, z) = Σ z^|S| over independent sets S
  At z=2: Z = H (Hamiltonian path count)
  At z=1: Z = number of independent sets
  At z→∞: Z ~ z^α(Ω) (dominated by max independent set)

p=5 Interval: 5 3-cycles, 1 5-cycles
  Total odd cycles: 6

